! Dev Workflow

!! Local install

```
# in dev-wiki/
python3 -m venv .venv
.venv/bin/pip install -r plugins/rimir/msg-import/scripts/requirements.txt
# merge plugins/rimir/msg-import/runner-actions/msg.json into runner-actions.json
# restart the server
```

(System pip is blocked on Debian/Ubuntu 24.04+ by PEP 668. The runner-action commands reference `.venv/bin/python3` relative to `$tw.boot.wikiPath`. Swap for system `python3` if you installed extract-msg another way.)

!! Smoke test without the wiki

The Python script runs standalone — no need to drop a file through the UI to see what comes out. The same command handles `.msg` and `.eml` inputs (format auto-detected from filename extension):

```
cd dev-wiki
TW_WIKI_PATH="$(pwd)" .venv/bin/python3 plugins/rimir/msg-import/scripts/extract.py \
  --mode=body \
  --input "$(pwd)/files/email/some.msg" \
  --attach-dir "$(pwd)/files/email/_derived/some.msg/" \
  --source-uri "/files/email/some.msg" \
  > /tmp/out.md
```

Inspect `/tmp/out.md` — should start with `---` (YAML frontmatter) and contain the markdown body. Inline images appear under `_derived/some.msg/cid_*.<ext>`.

For attachments:

```
TW_WIKI_PATH="$(pwd)" .venv/bin/python3 plugins/rimir/msg-import/scripts/extract.py \
  --mode=attachments \
  --input "$(pwd)/files/email/some.msg" \
  --attach-dir "$(pwd)/files/email/_derived/some.msg/att_" \
  --source-uri "/files/email/some.msg"
```

Returns a JSON summary on stdout. Files land in `_derived/some.msg/` with the `att_` prefix.

!! Restart rules

* The pipeline tiddler (`pipelines/msg.tid`) and config tiddlers are re-read per request — no restart.
* `runner-actions.json` is loaded at boot only by both `rimir/runner` and `rimir/file-pipeline` — restart after merging the snippet.
* The Python script is read every time the runner shells out — no restart needed when iterating on it.

!! Iterating on the extractor

When tweaking `extract.py`, run the standalone smoke test above. Drop the same `.msg` again through the UI; file-upload's content-hash dedup will reject the duplicate parent, but you can delete the parent tiddler first (and let cascade clean up the artifacts) before re-dropping.

!! Files at a glance

| !File | !What it does |
| `pipelines/msg.tid` | Pipeline def — MIME match list (`vnd.ms-outlook` + `rfc822`) + 4 steps |
| `cascade/msg.tid` / `cascade/eml.tid` | ViewTemplateBodyFilter entries — `.msg` and `.eml` parents both dispatch to `body/msg` |
| `runner-actions/msg.json` | Whitelisted runner actions (snippet to merge — handles both formats via the same script) |
| `scripts/extract.py` | Format-dispatched extractor — `.msg` via the `extract-msg` lib, `.eml` via Python's stdlib `email` module. ''Don't rename to `extract_msg.py`'' — that shadows the library and `import extract_msg` resolves to the script itself, breaking the API |
| `prompts/email-summary.tid` | LLM prompt template for the optional summary step |
| `config/llm-summary.tid` | Toggle for the summary step (default: `no`) |
| `config/quarantine-executables.tid` | Toggle for `.exe`/`.bat`/... blocking (default: `yes`) |
